#### 1. Destructor Pattern for Resource Cleanup
In the context of ESP-IDF based projects using C++ wrappers around low-level drivers (such as `led_strip`), it's essential to properly deinitialize and free resources in the destructor. This includes stopping timers, clearing LED states, and deleting handles.

```cpp
SingleLed::~SingleLed()
{
    if (blink_timer_) {
        esp_timer_stop(blink_timer_);
        esp_timer_delete(blink_timer_);
    }

    if (led_strip_) {
        led_strip_clear(led_strip_);
        led_strip_del(led_strip_);
    }
}
```

This pattern ensures that any allocated hardware or software resources are safely released when the object goes out of scope or is explicitly deleted. It avoids memory leaks and potential crashes due to dangling pointers or active timers after destruction.

