std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(mutex_);
```

This line appears consistently across functions like `TurnOn`, `TurnOff`, `StartBlinkTask`, and `OnBlinkTimer`.

Apply this same locking mechanism inside the destructor if there’s any chance of concurrent access during destruction (e.g., from a running timer callback). However, since destructors are usually called under controlled circumstances, additional synchronization may not always be necessary unless asynchronous callbacks are involved.

