- Frame duration
- Session ID
- Supported features or protocols

A typical server hello might look like:
```json
{
  "type": "hello",
  "session_id": "abcd1234",
  "audio_params": {
    "sample_rate": 24000,
    "frame_duration": 60
  },
  "features": {
    "aec": true
  }
}
```

So in `ParseServerHello`, you would do something like:
```cpp
void WebsocketProtocol::ParseServerHello(const cJSON *root)
{
    auto session_obj = cJSON_GetObjectItem(root, "session_id");
    if (cJSON_IsString(session_obj)) {
        session_id_ = session_obj->valuestring;
    }

    auto audio_params = cJSON_GetObjectItem(root, "audio_params");
    if (cJSON_IsObject(audio_params)) {
        auto sample_rate_obj = cJSON_GetObjectItem(audio_params, "sample_rate");
        if (cJSON_IsNumber(sample_rate_obj)) {
            server_sample_rate_ = sample_rate_obj->valueint;
        }

        auto frame_duration_obj = cJSON_GetObjectItem(audio_params, "frame_duration");
        if (cJSON_IsNumber(frame_duration_obj)) {
            server_frame_duration_ = frame_duration_obj->valueint;
        }
    }

    // Signal event group that we've received the server hello
    xEventGroupSetBits(event_group_handle_, WEBSOCKET_PROTOCOL_SERVER_HELLO_EVENT);
}
```

This follows the same pattern seen elsewhere in the codebase where JSON responses are parsed into member variables and events are signaled accordingly.

